@startuml
!theme plain

title AAS Sequence - Podman Build and Kubernetes Runtime Flow

actor "Developer / Platform Engineer" as Dev
participant "Podman CLI" as Podman
participant "Container Registry" as Registry
participant "kubectl" as Kubectl
participant "Kubernetes API Server" as K8sAPI
participant "Deployment\nuim-sap-aas" as Deployment
participant "Pod\nuim-sap-aas-service" as Pod
participant "Service\nuim-sap-aas" as Service
participant "HPA\nuim-sap-aas" as HPA
participant "Metrics Server" as Metrics

Dev -> Podman : podman build -t uim-sap-aas:tag .
Podman --> Dev : Image built
Dev -> Podman : podman push <registry>/uim-sap-aas:tag
Podman -> Registry : Push image
Registry --> Podman : Image available

Dev -> Kubectl : kubectl apply -f k8s/*.yaml
Kubectl -> K8sAPI : Create/Update ConfigMap, Secret, Deployment, Service, HPA
K8sAPI -> Deployment : Reconcile desired state
Deployment -> Pod : Pull image and start container
Pod -> Pod : Expose :8086
K8sAPI -> Service : Bind selector app=uim-sap-aas
Service -> Pod : Route traffic to targetPort 8086

HPA -> Metrics : Read CPU/Memory utilization
Metrics --> HPA : Current metrics
HPA -> Deployment : Adjust replica count (2..8)
Deployment -> Pod : Scale out/in pods

note right of Pod
Endpoints served by container:
- /api/autoscaler/health
- /api/autoscaler/ready
- /api/autoscaler/apps
- /api/autoscaler/apps/{id}/metrics/evaluate/apply
end note

@enduml
